Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithms for graph problems, specifically Feedback Vertex Set, and introduces a new parameter called maximum induced matching width (mim-width). This parameter is related to tree-width and clique-width, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses the mim-width of various graph classes, such as Interval graphs and Permutation graphs, which are often studied in the sub-categories of cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper presents a polynomial-time algorithm for Feedback Vertex Set on graphs of bounded mim-width, which is a fundamental graph problem and falls under the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
